CONTINENTAL
AIRLINES
System Timetable
August 1, 1985
An Australian
Adventure

AN AUSTRALIAN ADVENTURE
Continental Airlines invites you to enjoy our
inflight "Australian Adventure.
" Often
referred to as the wonder "down under,"
Australia is the land of great and unusual
beauty,
home of some of the world's most
breathtaking sights and oddest animals. It is
home to the Great Barrier Reef, the largest
living thing on earth, and Ayer's Rock, the
world's largest monolith. Australia is the
natural habitat of kangaroos, koalas, emus
and platypuses.
An inflight video on board Continental's
domestic U.S. DC10 flights will introduce
you to the wonders of Australia. On selected
flights you'll have a chance to taste the
full-bodied wines of Australia, and fine
Australian lagers will be available on all
flights. Enjoy the music of well-known
Australian popular entertainers on channel 3
of Continental's Golden Marquee stereo
program while sampling hearty Australian
cheeses.
Continental has fourteen conveniently
scheduled weekly round trip flights between
the U.S. and Australia. Flights to both
Melbourne and Sydney depart the U.S. via
Honolulu from both Los Angeles and San
Francisco, with connecting service available
from other Continental cities.
So experience the world "down under" for
yourself... on Continental!
